  "body": "Presently there's 1 test for `process_sync_committee_updates` that checks the transition from period 0 to period 1. This is an exceptional case, because the `base_epoch` for both period 0 and period 1 is epoch 0.\r\n\r\nIn Lighthouse, I had written an erroneous bounds check that looked like this:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n if base_epoch != current_base_epoch\r\n     && base_epoch != current_base_epoch.safe_add(spec.epochs_per_sync_committee_period)?\r\n {\r\n    return Err(Error::EpochOutOfBounds);\r\n }\r\n ```\r\n \r\nIt failed as soon as I tried transitioning from period 1 to period 2, because `process_sync_committee_updates` tried to calculate the sync committee for period 3, which has `base_epoch == 2 * EPOCHS_PER_SYNC_COMMITTEE_PERIOD` which is not equal to the `current_base_epoch` (0) + `EPOCHS_PER_SYNC_COMMITTEE_PERIOD`.\r\n\r\nI think it would be good to test a period transition from a period other than 0 to catch mistakes like this.",
